reviews.reviewText: I bought these to hold my toiling cadence capsules and it is a perfect fit. I ordered two thinking that it would be easier to pack two smaller bags than the one large bag. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Amazon purchase in a while
reviews.reviewText: As other reviews have said, this is the perfect, affordable but still high quality dupe of a different, wildly expensive brand. The bag is TSA compliant which was the most important thing for me, but it is also well made, very sturdy, and the shape of it makes it easy to organize my liquids by laying them down rather than forcing them all to stand up. Even the packaging was beautiful. 10/10 would reccomend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than its luxury competitor
reviews.reviewText: I bought this makeup bag because it looks like a MUCH more expensive one that I have wanted to buy. I bought the expensive one (brand name starts with a T) thinking it would be a better, more sturdy bag, better zipper, etc. Wrong. This one is actually better in a couple of areas: it has thicker, more sturdy plastic "windows", and the zipper is tighter and seems as good or smoother than the T one. The T brand does have cooler colors (more neutrals which make them look more $$) and you just have to decide if that is worth 4 or 5 times the price of this one. Yes, you read that right. Otherwise, they seem very similar in style, quality of material, size. They both could use a loop handle, however. Overall I am pleased with its size (will fit into a carry on) and love the look / style. And I love that there are windows on each side, allowing me to see eactly what's inside.
